msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kde\">K Desktop Environment</"
"ulink>; a project to develop a free graphical desktop environment for &UNIX; "
"compatible systems."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kde\">K Desktop Okruženje</ulink>; "
"projekt da se razvije besplatno grafičko desktop okruženje za &UNIX; "
"kompatibilne sisteme."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Binding"
msgstr "Mapiranje Tipki"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:183
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "All features of &krusader; are available through the menubar, but you can "
#| "also bind (link) a certain key combination to that function. You will "
#| "find, however, that using the <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands"
#| "\">keyboard</link> is remarkably faster than using the menubar or <link "
#| "linkend=\"gloss-gui\">GUI</link>. <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands"
#| "\">Keyboard usage</link> is an important tool for <link linkend=\"gloss-"
#| "ofm\">Orthodox File Managers</link>. &krusader; comes with several "
#| "predefined <link linkend=\"key_bindings\">Key Bindings</link>."
msgid ""
"All features of &krusader; are available through the menubar, but you can "
"also bind (link) a certain key combination to that function. You will find, "
"however, that using the <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands\">keyboard</link> "
"is remarkably faster than using the menubar or <link linkend=\"gloss-gui"
"\">&GUI;</link>. <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands\">Keyboard usage</link> "
"is an important tool for <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">Orthodox File Managers</"
"link>. &krusader; comes with several predefined <link linkend=\"key_bindings"
"\">Key Bindings</link>."
msgstr ""
"Sve pogodnosti &krusader; su dostupne na meniju, ali možete da povežete "
"(link) sa odeđenom kombinacijom tipki za tu funkciju. Međutim, otkrit ćete "
"da prilikom korištenja <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands\">tastature</link> "
"je znatno brže nego korištenje menu bara ili <link linkend=\"gloss-gui"
"\">GUI</link>. <link linkend=\"keyboard-commands\">Iskoristivost tastature</"
"link> je važan alat za <link linkend=\"gloss-ofm\">Orthodox File Managers</"
"link>. &krusader; dolazi sa nekoliko unaprijed definisanih<link linkend="
"\"key_bindings\">Povezanih tipki</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid "KPart"
msgstr "KPart"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:200
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KPart\">KPart</ulink>; KParts "
#| "is the name of the component framework for the &kde; desktop environment. "
#| "KParts are analogous to Bonobo components in <ulink url=\"http://www."
#| "gnome.org\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, both of which are "
#| "based on the same concepts as &Microsoft;'s Object Linking and Embedding. "
#| "&eg; if you use &krusader;'s viewer to view a PDF file, &okular; will be "
#| "launched inside &krusader;'s viewer."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KPart\">KPart</ulink>; KParts is "
"the name of the component framework for the &kde; desktop environment. "
"KParts are analogous to Bonobo components in <ulink url=\"https://www.gnome."
"org\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, both of which are based on "
"the same concepts as &Microsoft;'s Object Linking and Embedding. &eg; if you "
"use &krusader;'s viewer to view a &PDF; file, &okular; will be launched "
"inside &krusader;'s viewer."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KPart\">KPart</ulink>; KParts je "
"ime komponente framework-a za &kde; desktop okruženja. KParts su analogni "
"prema Bonobo komponentama <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org"
"\"><application>GNOME</application></ulink>, od kojih su oba bazirana na "
"istim konceptima kao &Microsoft;ov Povezni sistem. &eg; ako koristite "
"&krusader;ov posmatrač da vidite PDF fajl, &okular; će biti pokrenut unutar "
"&krusader;ovog posmatrača."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>KIO</acronym> or kioslave"
msgstr "<acronym>KIO</acronym> ili kioslave"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:216
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kioslave\">KDE Input/Output</"
#| "ulink>; also known as KIO Slaves is part of the &kde; architecture. It "
#| "provides access to files, web sites and other resources through a single "
#| "consistent API."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kioslave\">KDE Input/Output</"
"ulink>; also known as KIO Slaves is part of the &kde; architecture. It "
"provides access to files, web sites and other resources through a single "
"consistent API."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kioslave\">KDE Input/Output</"
"ulink>; poznat i kao KIO Slaves je dio od &kde; architekture. On osigurava "
"pristup fajlovima, web stranicama i drugim resursima preko jednog "
"konzistentnog API."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "mount"
msgstr "montiraj"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:227
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_%28computing%29\"> "
#| "Mounting</ulink>; in computer science, is the process of making a file "
#| "system ready for use by the operating system, typically by reading "
#| "certain index data structures from storage into memory ahead of time. The "
#| "term recalls a period in the history of computing when an operator had to "
#| "mount a magnetic tape or hard disk on a spindle before using it."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_%28computing%29\"> "
"Mounting</ulink>; in computer science, is the process of making a file "
"system ready for use by the operating system, typically by reading certain "
"index data structures from storage into memory ahead of time. The term "
"recalls a period in the history of computing when an operator had to mount a "
"magnetic tape or hard disk on a spindle before using it."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_%28computing%29\"> "
"Mountiranje</ulink>; je u kompjuterskoj nauci proces pripremanja sistemskog "
"fajla da bude spreman za korištenje u operativnom sistemu, tipično je to "
"čitanje određenih struktura podataka iz skladišta u memoriju prije upotrebe. "
"Izraz podsjeća na vrijeme u historiji računara kada je operator morao da "
"montira magnetnu traku ili hard disk na osovinu prije upotrebe."

#. Tag: acronym
#: glossary.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>OFM</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>OFM</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:243
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://www.softpanorama.org/OFM/index.shtml\"> Orthodox File "
#| "Manager</ulink>; also known as \"Commanders\". Members of this family of "
#| "file managers use simple yet very powerful interface that is a direct "
#| "derivative of the <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
#| "Norton_Commander\"> Norton Commander</ulink> (NC) interface."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.softpanorama.org/OFM/index.shtml\"> Orthodox File "
"Manager</ulink>; also known as <quote>Commanders</quote>. Members of this "
"family of file managers use simple yet very powerful interface that is a "
"direct derivative of the <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Norton_Commander\"> Norton Commander</ulink> (NC) interface."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://www.softpanorama.org/OFM/index.shtml\"> Orthodox File "
"Manager</ulink>; poznat i kao \"Zapovjednici\". Članovi ove grupe fajl "
"menadžera koriste jednostavano, ali vrlo moćno sučelje koje je direktno "
"izvedeno iz <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norton_Commander\"> "
"Norton Commander</ulink> (NC) sučelja."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>RPM</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>RPM</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the binary file format for distributions based on the <ulink url="
"\"http://www.rpm.org/\">RPM Package Manager</ulink>, a widely used packaging "
"tool for the &Linux; operating system. If you still have to get &krusader; "
"and your system supports RPM packages, you should get &krusader; packages "
"ending in <literal role=\"extension\">.rpm</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je binarni format fajla za distribuciju koji je baziran <ulink url="
"\"http://www.rpm.org/\">RPM Package Manager</ulink>, široko korišteni paket "
"za &Linux; operativni sistem. Ako i dalje želite da dobijete &krusader; i "
"ako vaš sistem podžava RPM pakete, trebali bi dobiti &krusader; pakete koji "
"završavaju u <literal role=\"extension\">.rpm</literal>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>SSH</acronym>, Secure Shell"
msgstr "<acronym>SSH</acronym>, Sigurna zaštita"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:269
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SSH\">SSH</ulink>; is a set of "
#| "standards and an associated network protocol that allows establishing a "
#| "secure channel between a local and a remote computer."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SSH\">SSH</ulink>; is a set of "
"standards and an associated network protocol that allows establishing a "
"secure channel between a local and a remote computer."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SSH\">SSH</ulink>; je grupa "
"standarda i povezanih mrežnih protokola koji dozvoljavaju upostavljanje "
"sigurnog kanala između lokalnog i daljinskog kompjutera."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>SVN</acronym>, Subversion"
msgstr "<acronym>SVN</acronym>, Subverzija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:279
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subversion\"> Subversion</"
#| "ulink>; a version control system that is a compelling replacement for "
#| "<link linkend=\"gloss-cvs\">CVS</link>. It is used by many software "
#| "projects including &kde;."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subversion\"> Subversion</ulink>; "
"a version control system that is a compelling replacement for <link linkend="
"\"gloss-cvs\">CVS</link>. It is used by many software projects including "
"&kde;."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subversion\"> Subverzija</ulink>; "
"verzija kontrolnog sistema koja je adekvatna zamjena za <link linkend="
"\"gloss-cvs\">CVS</link>. Koristi se u mnoštvu softverskih projekata "
"uključujući i &kde;."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminal emulator"
msgstr "Emulator terminala"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:290
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminal_emulator\"> Terminal "
#| "emulator</ulink>; simply a windowed shell; this is known as command line "
#| "window in some other environments. If you want to use the shell and type "
#| "the commands, you should know at least a few of the system-level commands "
#| "for your operating system."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminal_emulator\"> Terminal "
"emulator</ulink>; simply a windowed shell; this is known as command line "
"window in some other environments. If you want to use the shell and type the "
"commands, you should know at least a few of the system-level commands for "
"your operating system."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminal_emulator\"> Terminal "
"emulator</ulink>; jednostavna prozorska zaštita; ovo je poznato kao prozor "
"za komandne linije i za neka druga okruženja. Ako želite da koristite "
"zaštitu i da ukucate komande, trebali bi da znate bar nekoliko sistemskih "
"komandnih nivoa za vaš operativni sistem."

#. Tag: acronym
#: glossary.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "POSIX"
msgstr "POSIX"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:304
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posix\">Portable Operating "
#| "System Interface for uniX</ulink>; a collective name of a family of "
#| "related standards specified by the IEEE to define the application "
#| "programming interface (API) for software compatible with variants of the "
#| "&UNIX; operating system."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posix\">Portable Operating System "
"Interface for uniX</ulink>; a collective name of a family of related "
"standards specified by the IEEE to define the application programming "
"interface (API) for software compatible with variants of the &UNIX; "
"operating system."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posix\">Prenosivo sistemsko "
"sučelje za uniX</ulink>; kolektivno ime za grupu povezanih standarda "
"specificiranih od strane IEEE da definiše programsku aplikaciju sučelja "
"(API) za softver kompatibilan sa varijantama &UNIX; operativnog sistema."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "&URL;"
msgstr "&URL;"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:318
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL\">Universal Resource "
#| "Locator</ulink>; a universal resource locator is the technical term for "
#| "what is commonly referred to as a websites address. Examples of &URL;s "
#| "include <ulink url=\"http://krusader.sourceforge.net\"> http://krusader."
#| "sourceforge.net</ulink> and <link linkend=\"remote-connections\">Remote "
#| "Connections</link>."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL\">Universal Resource Locator</"
"ulink>; a universal resource locator is the technical term for what is "
"commonly referred to as a websites address. Examples of &URL;s include "
"<ulink url=\"https://krusader.org\"> https://krusader.org</ulink> and <link "
"linkend=\"remote-connections\">Remote Connections</link>."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL\">Univerzalni Resursni "
"Pretraživač</ulink>; univerzalni resursni pretraživač je tehnički pojam za "
"ono što se obično veže za web stranice. Primjeri za &URL; uključuju <ulink "
"url=\"http://krusader.sourceforge.net\"> http://krusader.sourceforge.net</"
"ulink> i <link linkend=\"remote-connections\">Daljinske Konekcije</link>."

#. Tag: acronym
#: glossary.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>VFS</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>VFS</acronym>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:333
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<link linkend=\"vfs\">Virtual file systems (VFS)</link> is a basic <link "
#| "linkend=\"features\">OFM feature</link>, this an abstracted layer over "
#| "all kinds of archived information (ZIP files, &FTP; servers, TAR "
#| "archives, NFS filesystems, SAMBA shares, ISO CD/DVD images, RPM catalogs, "
#| "&etc;), which allows the user to access all the information in these "
#| "divergent types of file systems transparently - just like entering an "
#| "ordinary sub-directory! &krusader; supports several <link linkend=\"vfs"
#| "\">Virtual file systems (VFS)</link>."
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"vfs\">Virtual file systems (VFS)</link> is a basic <link "
"linkend=\"features\">OFM feature</link>, this an abstracted layer over all "
"kinds of archived information (ZIP files, &FTP; servers, TAR archives, &NFS; "
"filesystems, SAMBA shares, ISO &CD;/&DVD; images, RPM catalogs, &etc;), "
"which allows the user to access all the information in these divergent types "
"of file systems transparently - just like entering an ordinary sub-folder! "
"&krusader; supports several <link linkend=\"vfs\">Virtual file systems "
"(VFS)</link>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"vfs\">Virtuelni sistemski fajl (VFS)</link> je osnovni <link "
"linkend=\"features\">OFM svojstvo</link>, to je zamišljeni sloj svakakvih "
"arhiviranih informacija (ZIP fajlovi, &FTP; serveri, TAR arhive, NFS "
"sistemski fajlovi, SAMBA djeljenja, ISO CD/DVD images, RPM katalozi, &etc;), "
"ko dozvoljava korisniku da pristupi svim informacijama u ovim divergentnim "
"tipovima sistemskih transparentnih fajlova, kao ulazak u određeni "
"poddirektorij! &krusader; podržava nekoliko <link linkend=\"vfs\">Virtuelnih "
"sistemskih fajlova (VFS)</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "&XML;"
msgstr "&XML;"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:347
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xml\">Extensible Markup "
#| "Language</ulink>; a very flexible text format derived from SGML (ISO "
#| "8879). Originally designed to meet the challenges of large-scale "
#| "electronic publishing, &XML; is also playing an increasingly important "
#| "role in the exchange of a wide variety of data on the Web and elsewhere."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xml\">Extensible Markup Language</"
"ulink>; a very flexible text format derived from SGML (ISO 8879). Originally "
"designed to meet the challenges of large-scale electronic publishing, &XML; "
"is also playing an increasingly important role in the exchange of a wide "
"variety of data on the Web and elsewhere."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xml\">Extensible Markup Language</"
"ulink>; veoma fleksibilan tekstualni format SGML (ISO 8879). Originalno "
"dizajniran da se nosi sa izazovima velikih razmjera elektronskih izdavanja, "
"&XML; također igra važnu ulogu u zamjeni širokog spektra podataka na Webu i "
"drugdje.\n"
"\t\n"
"."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zeroconf"
msgstr "Zeroconf"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:359
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeroconf\">Zeroconf</ulink>; or "
#| "Zero Configuration Networking is a set of techniques that automatically "
#| "create a usable IP network without configuration or special servers. This "
#| "allows inexpert users to connect computers, networked printers, and other "
#| "items together and expect them to work automatically."
msgid ""
"<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeroconf\">Zeroconf</ulink>; or "
"Zero Configuration Networking is a set of techniques that automatically "
"create a usable IP network without configuration or special servers. This "
"allows inexpert users to connect computers, networked printers, and other "
"items together and expect them to work automatically."
msgstr ""
"<ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeroconf\">Zeroconf</ulink>; ili "
"Nulta Mrežna Konfiguracija je skup tehnika koje automatski kreira "
"iskoristivu IP mrežu bez konfiguracije ili specijalnih servera. Ovo "
"dozvoljava neiskusnim korisnicima da se konektuju na računare, mrežne "
"printere i ostale predmete zajedno i očekujući da rade automatski."
